Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Trim, peel, and
cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch pieces (halve lengthwise first if
carrots are on the larger side).

Toss chickpeas on one side of a #baking sheet{} with half the
@veggie stock concentrate{1}, half the @Shawarma spice blend{1%tablespoon}, a drizzle
of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss carrots on empty side of
baking sheet with remaining @Shawarma spice blend{1%tablespoon}, another drizzle
of cooking oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until chickpeas are browned and crispy and carrots are browned
and tender, ~{18-22%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine rice{3/4%cup},
half the @chili powder{1/2%teaspoon} (you'll use more later), remaining
@veggie stock concentrate{1}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil,
then reduce to simmer; cover and cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter
@lemon{1}. Mince @jalapeño{1}(remove ribs and seeds for less heat). Roughly chop
@pistachios{1/2%ounce}.

> Pat chicken or salmon dry with paper towels and season all over with salt and
> pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken
> or salmon (skin sides down); cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per
> side, or cook salmon until skin is crisp, 5-7 minutes, then flip and cook until
> cooked through, 1-2 minutes more. Transfer to a cutting board to rest.

Pat @skin-on salmon{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with salt
and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
salmon (skin sides down); cook until skin is crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}, then flip and
cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to
rest.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over high heat. Add
@grape tomatoes{4%ounce}; cook, stirring occasionally, until blistered,
~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat; season with salt and pepper.

== Schug Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine parsley, @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon},
remaining @chili powder{1/2%teaspoon}, @olive oil{1 1/2%tablespoon},
a big squeeze of lemon juice, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with salt and
pepper.

== Lemon Aioli ==

In a separate small bowl, combine @vegan mayo{4%tablespoon},
remaining @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon}, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon},
a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of lemon zest. Add water
@water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with
salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in a drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} and season
with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with chickpeas, carrots, and tomatoes. Drizzle
everything with lemon aioli and schug sauce. Garnish with pistachios and serve with
any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing salmon); serve chicken or salmon atop bowls.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.